canonical:
  title: 伯牙
  author: 申沆
  language: lzh
  text: 我自彈吾琴不須求賞音鍾期亦何物強辨絃上心
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 伯牙
  author: 申沆
  language: lzh
  text: 我自彈吾琴。不須求賞音。鍾期亦何物。強辨絃上心。
korean:
  title: 백아
  author: 신항
  language: kor
  text: |-
    내 스스로 내 거문고를 타노니
    이 소리 알아줄 이 구하지 않는다
    종기라는 그 어떤 인물인가
    억지로 줄 위의 마음을 지껄이네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_010_0130&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Bak-a
  author: Shin Hang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I play my own zither,
    not seeking ears to praise its sound.
    What is this Zhong Qi to me?
    Why force the heart upon the strings to speak?
  footnotes:
    - Zhong Qi (鍾期) was a legendary figure in ancient Chinese tradition, known as the ultimate listener who understood the music of the great musician Bak-a (伯牙). This poem subverts that famous tale of musical understanding, suggesting that true artistry needs no witness.
